;; ooyake 公 — gov-units.g20-centralbanks.edn
;;
;; REAL DATA — the G20 central banks (monetary-authority dimension, distinct from the
;; finance ministries in gov-units.g20.edn). Per founder directive "demo じゃなくて
;; 実データ, G20". Every row :sourcing :authoritative + :verification-status
;; :maintainer-verified; each Wikidata QID independently verified against
;; wikidata.org and each :official-url / :provenance = the bank's OWN official site
;; (本体の url), on 2026-06-03.
;;
;; Modelled as :level :agency, :branch :independent (central banks are statutorily
;; independent monetary authorities — descriptive, never ranked). Parent = the
;; country unit (gov.<iso>) defined in gov-units.seed.edn / gov-units.g20.edn.
;;
;; The EU's central bank is the European Central Bank (parent gov.eu). The euro-area
;; national central banks (Banque de France / Bundesbank / Banca d'Italia) are listed
;; under their nations AND are part of the Eurosystem — both facts are true; this
;; file records the national central bank per G20 member + the ECB for the EU.
;;
;; Same gating as the rest of the real-data set: live kotoba ingest (KOTOBA_TOKEN)
;; and public /.well-known publication remain separate operator/Council steps.

